sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: Cryptococcus neoformans Database in Synthetic Biology Open Language
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: This is a collection of Biological Genetic Parts of Cryptococcus neoformans containing 23 different promoters, coding sequences and terminators, which were previously used and whose efficacy has already been proven in this organism. This work was made in order to facilitate the build and assembly of genetic circuits and plasmids for the study of this pathogen.
sbol:Collection.dc:creator: Sophia Garcia de Resende
sbol:Collection.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a collection of Biological Genetic Parts of Cryptococcus neoformans containing 23 different promoters, coding sequences and terminators, which were previously used and whose efficacy has already been proven in this organism. This work was made in order to facilitate the build and assembly of genetic circuits and plasmids for the study of this pathogen.
sbol:Collection.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts were obtain through a extensive literature review and by search of plasmids in databases such as NCBI and AddGene.

sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: Cryptococcus neoformans Database in Synthetic Biology Open Language
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: This is a collection of Biological Genetic Parts of Cryptococcus neoformans containing 23 different promoters, coding sequences and terminators, which were previously used and whose efficacy has already been proven in this organism. This work was made in order to facilitate the build and assembly of genetic circuits and plasmids for the study of this pathogen.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HOG1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubi H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the terminator of mitogen-activated protein kinase (HOG1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This terminator is delimited by primers present in the reference article. There is a SNP in relation to the genomic sequence (CP003830). We used the genomic sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GPD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans JEC21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter of glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sequence was directly sent personally by Dr. Chen Ding. We did a BLAST and found a deletion of five nucleotides in comparison with the Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans JEC21 chromosome sequence. Thus, we used the genomic sequence (AE017346).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ACT1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubii H99 (Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is actin's promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The plasmid pSDMA66 (#128355) sequence has an A in position 84, and the chromosome sequence has a G. We used the last one.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Plasmid pSDMA66 (#12835) GenBank: CP003820 Region: 1242235..12430676

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: amdS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A strain H99O
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the acetamidase coding sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: amdS as a selective marker for C. neoformans.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CnU6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans JEC21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the U6 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Specific to RNApol lII. Available on Reference Article's Supplementary Material. We couldn't find the correspondent GenBank ID because this sequence was too small.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Available on the Supplementary Material of WANG, et al. 2016.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: UGE2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubii H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter of the UDP-glucose epimerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter UGE2 is repressible by glucose and inducible by galactose. The 3' primer used to amplify the UGE2 promoter region encopassed the first codons of UGE2 protein. This region was, therefore, excluded from the promoter presented here, diminishing the size of this promoter from 1007 bp to 978 bp.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NAT (Nourseothricin Resistance/NrsR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A H99S strain
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of the Nourseothricin Resistance gene (NAT/NrsR).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We deleted the restriction enzyme sequence of NotI and added the atg codon the beginning of the sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GAL7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubii H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the galactose transferase promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter, GAL7 + 5'UTR, is repressible by glucose and inducible by galactose. The 3' primer used to amplify the GAL7 promoter region encopassed the first codon ATG. This ATG codon was, therefore, excluded from the promoter presented here, diminishing the size of this promoter from 1022 to 1020 bp.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TEF1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubi H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the terminator of the Elongation Factor 1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: TEF1 terminator has 100% identity to the Cryptococcus neoformans genomic sequence (CP003831).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A H99S strain
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of the Fluorescent Protein mCherry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The atg codon was added at the beginning of the sequence. The authors reported at the Addgene website that: “Addgene's sequencing results found K128R and Q193P mutations in mCherry. These mutations are not known to affect plasmid function”.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NEO (G418/Neomicin Resistance)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A strain H99O
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of the Neomycin Resistance gene (NEO/G418).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Present in plasmid pPEE33.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: URA5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans B-3501A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of the Orotidine Monophosphate Pyrophosphorylase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This genomic sequence (CM000046) is the same sequence described in the reference article (M34606).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Cas9
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubi H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of CRISPR associated protein 9 from the widely applied CRISPR-Cas system gene editing tool.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Originally, the Cas9 nucleotide sequence was PCR amplified from the Addgene plasmid #43802, and it has 2 SNPs in relation to the original one, but both sequences code the same aminoacid. At the C- terminal end of Cas9, there is the Nuclear Localization Signal (NLS), SV40 NLS.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: URA5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans B-3501A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter of the Orotidine Monophosphate Pyrophosphorylase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We did a BLAST with the article's sequence (M34606) and we found two deletions. Thus, the sequence provided here is the updated one, the genomic sequence (CM000046), which has 2 more bp.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TEF1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubi H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter of the Elongation Factor 1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The plasmid TEF1 sequence (#128354) has an SNP in position 168 compared to the genomic sequence (CP003831). We used the genomic sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CnU6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans JEC21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the U6 promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: That is an endogenous promoter of C. neoformans serotype D strain JEC21. The sequence is available on Reference Article's Supplementary Material and it presented 100% identity with C.neoformans genomic sequence (AE017348).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: URA5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans B-3501A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the terminator of the Orotidine Monophosphate Pyrophosphorylase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The Ura5 terminator (M34606) given by the reference has some SNPs compared to the genomic sequence (CM000046) present in this database.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A H99S
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of the Green Fluorescent Protein (GFP).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The atg codon was added at the beginning of the sequence. Present in plasmids: YSBE 508, YSBE 557 e YSBE 608 of the same article.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Plasmid YSBE 557 (#92085) Plasmid YSBE 608 (#92089) Plasmid YSBE 508 (#92081)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: APP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubii H99 (Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter of antiphagocytic protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In this article they renamed the previously isolated IP1 to antiphagocytic protein 1 (App1). The chromosome sequence (CP047908) has some SNP's and gaps compared to the article sequence (AF180108). We used the chromosome sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HYG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans serotype A strain H99O
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of the Hygromycin Resistance gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Present in plasmid pPEE38.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GAL7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. neoformans JEC21
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the galactose-1-fosfato uridililtransferase promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The GAL7 promoter is induced by galactose and repressed by glucose. The 3' primer used to amplify the GAL7 promoter region encopassed part of the first exon, therefore this part was excluded from the promoter presented here, diminishing the size of this promoter from 582 to 471 bp. Some SNPs were also detected in relation to the sequence presented in the original article, therefore the genomic sequence (AE017353) was used here.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GAL1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubii H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the galactose kinase promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter, GAL1 + 5'UTR, is repressible by glucose and inducible by galactose. The 3' primer used to amplify the GAL1 promoter region encompassed the first codon ATG. This ATG codon was, therefore, excluded from the promoter presented here, diminishing the size of this promoter from 978 to 976 bp.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TRP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Organism: Cryptococcus neoformans var. grubi H99
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator sequence of Phosphoribosylanthranilate Isomerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We used the genomic sequence (CP003828), that has a SNP, when compared with the sequence of the plasmids presented in the reference.

prov:Agent.dcterms:title: SBOLDesigner CAD Tool
prov:Agent.dcterms:description: SBOLDesigner is a simple, biologist-friendly CAD software tool for creating and manipulating the sequences of genetic constructs using the Synthetic Biology Open Language (SBOL) 2 data model. Throughout the design process, SBOL Visual symbols, a system of schematic glyphs, provide standardized visualizations of individual parts. SBOLDesigner completes a workflow for users of genetic design automation tools. It combines a simple user interface with the power of the SBOL standard and serves as a launchpad for more detailed designs involving simulations and experiments. Some new features in SBOLDesigner are the ability to add variant collections to combinatorial derivations, enumerating those collections, and the ability to view sequence features hierarchically. There are also some small changes to the way that preferences work in regards to saving a design with incomplete sequences.
